   =20
      Slorg didn=E2=80=99t burn Slerf
   =20
 =20

Yesterday=E2=80=99s column discussed a crypto project called Slerf that acc=
identally lost $10 million of money from buyers in its presale after its an=
onymous developer hit the wrong button; that developer=C2=A0then apologized=
 in an X Spaces session. I incorrectly attributed this mistake and apology =
to Slorg, another pseudonymous participant in the Space. It wasn=E2=80=99t =
Slorg, it was someone else; Slorg didn=E2=80=99t do anything wrong. Alas my=
 all-time favorite Money Stuff headline, =E2=80=9CSlorg Is Sorry He Burnt S=
lerf,=E2=80=9D was incorrect, and=C2=A0I apologize to Mr. Slorg.=C2=A0

