dth: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgro=
und-color: #ccc;">he can=E2=80=99t come up with the money</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Donald Trump said he reached out to the world=
=E2=80=99s biggest insurance companies to seek help in arranging an appeal =
bond covering the $454 million verdict against him in New York=E2=80=99s ci=
vil fraud suit, and none would take his real estate as collateral. They all=
 want cash and Trump says he doesn=E2=80=99t have enough.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The real estate mogul and former president wil=
l be forced to hold a =E2=80=9Cfire sale=E2=80=9D of his properties to rais=
e enough cash if the bond isn=E2=80=99t waived while he challenges the verd=
ict, Trump said in a filing Monday with a New York appeals court. The appea=
l bond is due March 25 if the requirement isn=E2=80=99t put on hold.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This, I should say, is somewhat weird. His who=
le argument is that his banks were in fact thrilled to lend him money, and =
that whatever was wrong in his financial statements didn=E2=80=99t matter b=
ecause the banks knew he was worth far more than they were lending him. Now=
, though, nobody will give him money. <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomber=
gbusiness.com/click/34741977.257361/aHR0cHM6Ly9hc3NldHMuYndieC5pby9kb2N1bWV=
udHMvdXNlcnMvaXFqV0hCRmRmeElVL3JJSG83SGxsNTNqQS92MA/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23=
cB40c57c23" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank=
" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-=
width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backg=
round-color: #ccc;">His lawyers</a> complain<a class=3D"footnote-index" hre=
