terest, exceeds $464 million, and very few bonding companies will consider =
a bond of anything approaching that=C2=A0magnitude. The remaining handful w=
ill not =E2=80=9Caccept hard assets such as real estate as collateral,=E2=
=80=9D but =E2=80=9Cwill only accept cash or cash equivalents (such as mark=
etable securities).=E2=80=9D Moreover, sureties would typically =E2=80=9Cre=
quire collateral of approximately 120% of the amount of the judgment,=E2=80=
=9D which =E2=80=9Cwould require Defendants to hand over collateral in the =
form of cash or cash equivalents of approximately=E2=80=9D $557 million.=C2=
=A0In addition, sureties would likely charge bond premiums of approximately=
 2 percent per year with two years in advance =E2=80=94 an upfront cost ove=
r $18 million.=C2=A0</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Where will Donald Trump get $557 million worth=
 of marketable securities by March 25? Oh=C2=A0man, do I have amazing news =
for him. The New York Times <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.=
com/click/34741977.257361/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cubnl0aW1lcy5jb20vMjAyNC8wMi8yNi9id=
XNpbmVzcy90cnVtcC1tZWRpYS1kaWdpdGFsLXdvcmxkLWFjcXVpc2l0aW9uLWNhc2guaHRtbA/6=
07f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB856fb870" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"items=
cope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !imp=
ortant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bott=
om-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">reported last month</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Former President Donald J. Trump=E2=80=99s sta=
ke in Trump Media &amp; Technology Group, his social media company, could b=
e worth as much as $4 billion once a long-delayed merger closes.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The deal, with Digital World Acquisition Corpo=
ration =E2=80=94 a publicly traded shell company =E2=80=94 could provide hi=
m with a potential financial lifeline at a time when he must come up with t=
he cash to pay a $454 million penalty after a New York judge=E2=80=99s ruli=
ng in a civil fraud case.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Digital World has scheduled a March 22 shareho=
lder vote on the merger with Trump Media, whose flagship product, Truth Soc=
ial, has become the social media platform of choice for Mr. Trump to attack=
 his critics and political opponents.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The shareholder vote is this Friday; the bond =
is due on Monday. Pretty tight! There are problems. For one thing, the shar=
eholders have to vote to approve the deal. They=C2=A0<em>obviously=C2=A0</e=
m>should do that: DWAC=E2=80=99s stock closed yesterday at $35.575 per shar=
e in anticipation of the deal; if the deal fails, shareholders will get bac=
k roughly $10.87 per share.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-8"=
