<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One possibility is that bribing government off=
icials is just routine in the world of global commodity trading. Here is a =
<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34741977.257361/aH=
R0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9mZWF0dXJlcy8yMDI0LXZpdG9sLW9pbC1icmliZXMvP=
2NtcGlkPUJCRDAzMTkyNF9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1u=
ZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTI0MDMxOSZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ce=
ef4b8524a319a23cBd6498a81" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" t=
arget=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important;=
 border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-styl=
e: solid; background-color: #ccc;">Bloomberg News story</a> about a former =
Vitol Group trader named Javier Aguilar, who was convicted last month=C2=A0=
of bribing Ecuadorian officials, and it seems like=C2=A0it would have been =
bigger news if he had=C2=A0<em>not=C2=A0</em>bribed them:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The revelations of the trial stretched far bey=
ond Javier Aguilar and Vitol, as witness after witness described a frenzied=
 period of corruption in Ecuador that extended across the oil trading indus=
try. On the very first day, a former Ecuadorian official stated flatly that=
 he had been bribed not just by Vitol, but also by Trafigura Group and Gunv=
or Group =E2=80=94 together, three of the four largest independent oil trad=
ers. (The other member of the quartet, Glencore Plc, has not been accused o=
f wrongdoing in Ecuador but in 2022 pleaded guilty to separate charges of c=
orruption in eight other countries.) =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">At one point Antonio Per=C3=A9 was asked if he=
 had ever helped a client with government business without paying a bribe t=
o a government official. =E2=80=9CI=E2=80=99m not sure,=E2=80=9D he replied=
. =E2=80=9CI cannot recall one.=E2=80=9D</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If you bribe one public official once in your =
life, I suppose you might be, like, giddy and awkward about it. But if you =
bribe every official on every deal, I would expect that you=E2=80=99d get p=
retty businesslike about it.=C2=A0If every deal involves a bribe, there wil=
l be professional networks of bribe consultants who will do the work in a p=
rofessional manner, and in fact there are:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">By adding more intermediary layers between cor=
rupt traders and corrupt government officials, the industry has fueled a th=
riving underbelly of =E2=80=9Cconsultants=E2=80=9D and =E2=80=9Cbrokers=E2=
=80=9D with bank accounts in opaque offshore jurisdictions.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CIn our country, in that area, it was =
common knowledge that in order to do business with the government, most of =
the time you had to pay bribes,=E2=80=9D Antonio Per=C3=A9 said.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Per=C3=A9 is a former Ecuadorian government em=
ployee who left to become a bribe consultant:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">By the time he met Aguilar, Per=C3=
=A9 and his brother Enrique had set themselves up as a one-stop shop for oi=
l traders looking to do business in Ecuador. In practice, they were a clear=
inghouse for bribes to Ecuadorian government officials.</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Which is a good business:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But it was the Per=C3=A9s who made=
 the fattest margins. Of the roughly $100 million they admitted receiving f=
rom oil traders seeking business in Ecuador, the brothers kept about half f=
or themselves.</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One advantage to all this professionalism, if =
you are paying or receiving bribes, is that it can create some deniability.=
 If on every deal you and all of your competitors pay consulting fees to a =
handful of consultants who work out of normal office buildings and have bus=
iness cards that say =E2=80=9Cenergy consultant,=E2=80=9D then if the autho=
rities ask questions you can say =E2=80=9Cah yes we had to pay that consult=
ant for consulting,=E2=80=9D and it will be a little hard for them to prove=
 that you did anything illegal. Perhaps at some point somebody hands a gove=
rnment official a sack of cash in a parking lot, but having=C2=A0<em>many=
=C2=A0</em>parts of the business look open and traceable and normal can giv=
e it all a veneer of legitimacy. The article features a spreadsheet of brib=
es. Businesslike!</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On the other hand, years of <a href=3D"https:/=
/link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34741977.257361/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxv=
b21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMTktMDEtMDQvZG9uLXQtY2FsbC1icmliZXM=
tY2hpY2tlbnM_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDMxOTI0X01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG=
1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjQwMzE5JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0d=
WZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB9bbd76f8" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"=
itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none=
 !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border=
-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">writing about bribery</a> ha=
s taught me that absolutely no one can resist the allure of talking in dumb=
 code that makes them look more guilty:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Sometimes their pseudo-spycraft veered towards=
 the absurd: they referred to Switzerland as the =E2=80=9Ccountry of cheese=
.=E2=80=9D Rather than naming Vitol=E2=80=99s competitors Trafigura and Gle=
ncore, they talked of =E2=80=9Cthe T and the G.=E2=80=9D ...</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">It was not just Ecuadorian officials that Vito=
l bribed via Hanst. He sent money to another middleman who handed it over, =
sometimes in a Houston parking lot, to employees of Mexico=E2=80=99s state =
oil company Pemex, who messaged each other excitedly about deliveries of =
=E2=80=9Ccandies.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Nobody=E2=80=99s going to read those messages =
and think you meant candies!</p>
